---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Departure: Fitness Quest">
  <section class="pt-16 pb-8 lg:pt-24 lg:pb-12">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-4">Built by lifters, for lifters.</h1>
      <p class="text-text-muted text-lg">The story behind Departure.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-surface border border-surface-light/50 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-text">The problem</h2>
          <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">
            Most fitness apps fall into two camps: serious workout trackers that are boring as hell, or gamified fitness apps that don't actually track real workouts. You're either staring at spreadsheets or doing "50 pushups to defeat the goblin."
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-muted">
            We wanted both. Real workout tracking — sets, reps, weight, personal records, progressive overload — wrapped in an RPG that actually makes you want to open the app. Not a gimmick. A game that rewards genuine effort.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-surface border border-surface-light/50 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-text">The solution</h2>
          <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">
            Departure tracks your actual training — every exercise, every set, every PR. Then it turns that data into RPG progression: XP, warrior stats, equipment drops, rank-ups. Your bench press doesn't just build your chest; it builds your Strength stat and helps your team defeat the Kraken.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-muted">
            The AI transformation feature lets you see what you could look like if you follow through. Not a fantasy. A realistic projection based on your body, goals, nutrition, and commitment level. It's a target you can chase.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-surface border border-surface-light/50 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-text">Anti-cheat? In a fitness app?</h2>
          <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">
            Yes. If XP means something, people will try to game it. Departure has a 6-layer anti-cheat system: weight limits per exercise category, personal best spike detection, daily workout caps, volume spike detection, and more. Every rule is transparent — you can see exactly how scoring works in-app.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-muted">
            We'd rather have honest Recruits than fake Legends.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-surface border border-surface-light/50 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-text">About Qualia AI</h2>
          <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">
            Departure is built by <strong class="text-text">Qualia AI</strong>, a consulting firm that builds AI-powered products. We use the same tech we deploy for enterprise clients — computer vision, generative AI, real-time data processing — to make fitness more engaging.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-muted">
            This isn't a side project. It's what happens when engineers who actually lift decide to build the app they wish existed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <div class="text-center mt-12">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Get in touch</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">Questions, feedback, or want to report a bug?</p>
        <a href="mailto:support@engagequalia.com" class="text-primary-light hover:text-primary transition-colors font-medium">
          support@engagequalia.com
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
